President Muhammadu Buhari has sent warm greetings to the former governor of Yobe State, Sen. Bukar Abba Ibrahim, on his 70th birthday. He praised him for living a life of service to humanity and encouraging budding leaders. In a statement by the Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Mallam Garba Shehu, the President said: “As you mark your birthday in good health, surrounded by family members and friends, which is one of greatest and happiest moments in one’s life, I convey to you my good wishes and that of the entire people of this country,” President Buhari said the former governor dedicated most of his life to public service, working for the state and nation for many years, speaking for the underprivileged as a lawmaker and inspiring youths to take up the mantle of leadership. “I wish you many more years of service and commitment to the nation. Happy birthday.”